headline: Intel shares rally after Trump hails the chipmaker’s progress
summary: Trump met with Intel Chief Executive Officer Lip-Bu Tan on Thursday at the White House, where the two men discussed the company’s new line of processors following the US government’s purchase of shares in the chipmaker.  In a post to his Truth Social network, Trump hailed recent advances at Santa Clara, California-based Intel, whose shares are up about 90% since plans emerged last year for the federal government to buy as much as 10% of the company.
